job_summary:
Responsibilities :- 

Manage the Intrusion prevention system, Endpoint Security Solution; 
Perform analysis, containment and remediation of security incidents; 
Ensure continuously enhancement of security tools and operations; 
Knowledgeable on information security trends and security standards; 
Install and operate security tools to protect systems and information infrastructure. 

Requirements :- 

Bachelor degree with at least 5 years’ relevant IT Security Operations experience; 
Relevant Information Security Certification; 
Basic understanding of malware analysis (Static and behavioral - optional) 
Knowledge of Cybersecurity practices, operation, risk management processes, principles, architecture, engineering, threat and vulnerabilities which includes incident response methodologies; 
Knowledge of intrusion prevention methodologies (IDS/IPS) techniques, Firewall, SIEM, Malware Analysis Sandbox and Endpoint Security Tools; 
Solid understanding of network protocols; 
Familiarity with multiple operating system (Windows and Unix); 
Programming experience on following programming language: Python and Powershell as an automation mindset; 
Good stakeholders’ management skills; able to collaborate with various high-performing teams and individual to accomplish common goals; 
Proactive, able to work with minimum supervision.
